83}}\n|-\n| shoddy || shorty || {{IPA|\u02c8\u0283\u0252\u02d0\u027ei}} || With [[intervocalic alveolar flapping]].\n|-\n| shot || short || {{IPA|\u02c8\u0283\u0252\u02d0t}}\n|-\n| snot || snort || {{IPA|\u02c8sn\u0252\u02d0t}}\n|-\n| sob || Sorb || {{IPA|\u02c8s\u0252\u02d0b}}\n|-\n| solder || sorter || {{IPA|\u02c8s\u0252\u02d0\u027e\u0259}} || With [[intervocalic alveolar flapping]].\n|-\n| sot || sort || {{IPA|\u02c8s\u0252\u02d0t}}\n|-\n| [[Spock]] || spork || {{IPA|\u02c8sp\u0252\u02d0k}}\n|-\n| spot || sport || {{IPA|\u02c8sp\u0252\u02d0t}}\n|-\n| stock || stork || {{IPA|\u02c8st\u0252\u02d0k}}\n|-\n| swan || sworn || {{IPA|\u02c8sw\u0252\u02d0n}}\n|-\n| swat || swart || {{IPA|\u02c8sw\u0252\u02d0t}}\n|-\n| tock || torque || {{IPA|\u02c8t\u0252\u02d0k}}\n|-\n| tot || tort || {{IPA|\u02c8t\u0252\u02d0t}}\n|-\n| tox || torques || {{IPA|\u02c8t\u0252\u02d0ks}}\n|-\n| wabble || warble || {{IPA|\u02c8w\u0252\u02d0b\u0259l}}\n|-\n| wad || ward || {{IPA|\u02c8w\u0252\u02d0d}}\n|-\n| wad || warred || {{IPA|\u02c8w\u0252\u02d0d}}\n|-\n| wan || warn || {{IPA|\u02c8w\u0252\u02d0n}}\n|-\n| wand || warned || {{IPA|\u02c8w\u0252\u02d0nd}}\n|-\n| wanna || Warner || {{IPA|\u02c8w\u0252\u02d0n\u0259}}\n|-\n| watt || wart || {{IPA|\u02c8w\u0252\u02d0t}}\n|-\n| whap || warp || {{IPA|\u02c8w\u0252\u02d0p}} || With [[wine\u2013whine merger]].\n|-\n| what || wart || {{IPA|\u02c8w\u0252\u02d0t}} || With [[wine\u2013whine merger]].\n|-\n| whop || warp || {{IPA|\u02c8w\u0252\u02d0p}} || With [[wine\u2013whine merger]].\n|-\n| wobble || warble || {{IPA|\u02c8w\u0252\u02d0b\u0259l}}\n|-\n| yock || [[York]] || {{IPA|\u02c8j\u0252\u02d0k}}\n|}\n\n=== Bud\u2013bird merger ===\nA merger of {{IPA|/\u025c\u02d0(r)/}}  and {{IPA|/\u028c/}}  occurring for some speakers of [[Jamaican English]] making ''bud'' and ''bird'' homophones as {{IPA|/b\u028cd/}}.<ref name=Wells>{{cite book | author=[[John C. Wells|Wells, John C.]] | title=Accents of English | location=[[Cambridge]] | publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]] | year=1982 | isbn=0-521-22919-7}}, pp. 136\u201337, 203\u20136, 234, 245\u201347, 339\u201340, 400, 419, 443, 576</ref><!-- Wells: 576 -->  The conversion of {{IPA|/\u025c\u02d0/}} to {{IPA|[\u028c]}} or {{IPA|[\u0259]}} is also found in places scattered around England and Scotland. Some speakers, mostly rural, in the area from [[London]] to [[Norfolk]] exhibit this conversion, mainly before voiceless fricatives. This gives pronunciation like ''first'' {{IPA|[f\u028cst]}} and ''worse'' {{IPA|[w\u028cs]}}. The word ''cuss'' appears to derive from the application of this sound change to the word ''curse''. Similarly, ''lurve'' is coined from ''love''.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\"\n|+ class=\"nowrap\" | Homophonous pairs\n! {{IPA|/\u028c/}}\n! {{IPA|/\u025c\u02d0r/}}\n! IPA\n! Notes\n|-\n| blood || blurred || {{IPA|\u02c8bl\u028cd}}\n|-\n| bub || burb || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028cb}}\n|-\n| buck || [[Burke (disambiguation)|Burke]] || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028ck}}\n|-\n| Buckley || Berkeley || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028ckli}}\n|-\n| bud || bird || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028cd}}\n|-\n| bud || burred || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028cd}}\n|-\n| budging || burgeon || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028cd\u0292\u0259n}} || With [[weak vowel merger]] and [[G-dropping]].\n|-\n| bug || berg || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028c\u0261}}\n|-\n| bug || burg || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028c\u0261}}\n|-\n| bugger || burger || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028c\u0261\u0259}}\n|-\n| bugging || bergen; [[Bergen]] || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028c\u0261\u0259n}} || With [[weak vowel merger]] and [[G-dropping]].\n|-\n| bummer || Burma || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028cm\u0259}}\n|-\n| bun || [[Bern]] || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028cn}}\n|-\n| bun || burn || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028cn}}\n|-\n| bunt || burnt || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028cnt}}\n|-\n| bused; bussed || burst || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028cst}}\n|-\n| bust || burst || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028cst}}\n|-\n| but || [[Bert (name)|Bert]] || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028ct}}\n|-\n| but || [[Burt (disambiguation)|Burt]] || {{IPA|\u02c8b\u028ct}}\n|